PGE, Polish Utility, Reappoints Zadroga as Chief Executive, Picks New CFO

-- B y   M a c i e j   M a r t e w i c z
-- 
2011-03-17T05:26:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/pge-polish-utility-reappoints-zadroga-as-chief-executive-picks-new-cfo.html
PGE SA, Poland’s largest power
utility, reappointed Tomasz Zadroga as chief executive officer
for his second term yesterday. The company also appointed
Wojciech Ostrowski, who previously worked at Czech Unipetrol AS,
as new chief financial officer after Wojciech Topolnicki was
dismissed in January.  Pawel Skowronski, currently with Vattanfall AB’s Polish
unit, will replace Marek Trawinski as chief operational officer.  The management’s new term starts on July 2.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maciej Martewicz at 
 mmartewicz@bloomberg.net  